UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 2133
1 A RESOLUTION honoring the survivors of crimes committed by Jeffrey Epstein
2 and his co-conspirators.
3 WHEREAS, for decades, numerous individuals were subjected to a systematic and
4 predatory network of sexual exploitation and human trafficking orchestrated by Jeffrey
5 Epstein; and
6 WHEREAS, the survivors of these heinous crimes have demonstrated extraordinary
7 courage by coming forward to tell their stories, a selfless act that has exposed the hidden
8 realities of human trafficking; and
9 WHEREAS, the personal accounts of survivors have been the primary catalyst for
10 uncovering the truth and demanding accountability for those who facilitated or ignored
11 the crimes of Jeffrey Epstein and his co-conspirators; and
12 WHEREAS, by sharing their stories, these survivors have paved a path toward
13 healing and empowered fellow survivors of sexual abuse and human trafficking; and
14 WHEREAS, the House of Representatives commends the survivors for their
15 bravery and willingness to speak the truth, often at great personal risk and in the face of
16 public scrutiny;
17 NOW, THEREFORE,
18 Be it resolved by the House of Representatives of the General Assembly of the
19 Commonwealth of Kentucky:
20 Section 1. The House of Representatives hereby recognizes and honors the
21 survivors of the Jeffrey Epstein trafficking network for their courage and resilience in the
22 face of incomprehensible harm.
23 Section 2. The House of Representatives stands in solidarity with all survivors
24 of sexual abuse and human trafficking, affirming that their stories deserve to be heard and
25 their healing is a priority for this Commonwealth.
26 Section 3. The Clerk of the House of Representatives is directed to transmit a
27 copy of this Resolution to Representative Mary Lou Marzian.
